      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ALFIE'S GIRL (5) was crowded for room and fell at The Gardens last time but prior to that was a 23.09 winner in a Maiden. Tough to beat on best and worth another try. BEAUTIFUL BANTER (2) made light work of a wide draw last time with a slick early sectional but gathered in and had to settle for the minors, finishing second (17.58) at this track over 300m. Got the money at her only try from this box. Leading chance. CAMARO ROSE (3) looks close to another win after finishing third last time (19.99) in a Maiden at Gunnedah. Comes out of a solid form race last start. Hard to beat again. OXLEY CHOICE (1) was below best last time at Q Parklands (42.93) in a Grade 5, finishing a 13 length fifth. Has already won three times from this draw.",
